data.name: Settings_EncryptionMode_Descr
data.value: Enter a positive integer value for encryption mode. Use "0" for machine-level RSA cryptoservice provider. Use "1" for AES provider with database stored private key.

data.name: Settings_DefaultCacheInterval_Descr
data.value: Certain frame types allow caching of the information they present in the DMP application local cache provider in order to avoid excessive network traffic and reduce the amount of CPU time taken to render such frames. This represents a default cache interval for a given type of frame when new frame is created. The value can be overriden for every frame.

data.name: Settings_DefaultDisplayErrorLength_Descr
data.value: Whenever errors occur in the frame content, displays will pop up a box with error message and additional details. Enter a positive integer number to tell DMP application displays how long to keep the error box visible. Enter zero value to suppress errors on a display. This is a default which can be overriden on individual displays.

data.name: Settings_DefaultDisplayPollInterval_Descr
data.value: Displays will poll their settings regularly following this time interval. When settings change the displays will automatically reload themselves. Enter a positive integer number. This is a default which can be overriden on individual displays.

data.name: Settings_DefaultDisplayReadyEventTimeout_Descr
data.value: Certain types of frames require additional initialization before they complete their rendering process on a display. They may either show blank or feature a loading indicator. DMP application will wait the above time period and, when exceeded, will leave the frame unrendered. This is a default which can be overriden on individual displays.

data.name: Settings_DefaultPanelFadeLength_Descr
data.value: Transition time between frames in a given panel can be augmented by entering a positive decimal number. Enter zero value for instant frame change without transition effects. This is a default which can be overriden on individual panels.

data.name: Settings_DefaultTemplate_Descr
data.value: Frames use HTML templates to render their content in. This represents a default template for a given type of frame when new frame is created. The value can be overriden for every frame.

data.name: Settings_EWSTracingPath_Descr
data.value: When you are experincing issues while registering EWS accounts in DMM application, enable EWS communication tracing by entering network path to the file which will receive the event log. Clear this setting to disable EWS tracing.

data.name: Settings_PresentationSite_Descr
data.value: Use this setting in cases when DMP application is installed on a different web site than DMM application.

data.name: Register_EnterNameForThisDisplay
data.value: Enter a name to call this display

data.name: Settings_DisplayAutoLoadMode_Descr
data.value: Automatic display resolution mode. Use "0" to recognize displays by host name or IP address. Use "1" to recognize displays by tracking cookie.
